:: StoryTitle
Crossfeed

:: StoryData
{
  "ifid": "70275269-981D-4791-B1D2-4A02CA8D20FE",
  "format": "SugarCube",
  "format-version": "2.37.3",
  "start": "FlightPrep"
}

:: StoryInit
/* SCENARIO TITLE:      Crossfeed
   AUDIENCE:            General Aviation Pilots (multi-engine)
   TONE:                Professional
   PRIMARY TOPIC:       Twin fuel-system management and the self-inflicted
                        engine failure (starvation, crossfeed logic, the
                        diagnose-before-you-secure discipline)
   SECONDARY TOPIC:     Night operations, diagnosis under uncertainty,
                        divert decisions
   AIRCRAFT/EQUIPMENT:  1978 Piper PA-34-200T Seneca II, N7462C. Two
                        counter-rotating turbocharged Continental TSIO-360s,
                        200 hp/side. 93 gal usable (46.5/side). Per-engine
                        fuel selectors ON / OFF / X-FEED. Electric boost
                        pumps. Oil-pressure prop feathering, no unfeathering
                        accumulators. JPI EDM-760 with fuel totalizer.
                        Vmc 66 KIAS, Vyse 89 KIAS.
   SETTING:             KSAT (San Antonio Intl) to KELP (El Paso Intl),
                        430 nm direct at 10,000. Saturday night in late
                        March, wheels up about 30 minutes after sunset.
                        Junction, Sonora, Ozona, Fort Stockton, Pecos, and
                        a great deal of nothing in between.
   WEATHER:             Night VMC. New moon. Thickening high cirrus over
                        the western half of the route masking the stars.
                        Light surface winds. Westerly winds aloft stronger
                        than forecast. No icing, no convection.
   ADM THEMES:          Per-side fuel math vs. total fuel math, habit
                        pattern disruption, diagnosis before commitment,
                        sunk-cost continuation, the divert that feels like
                        going backward.
   HAZARDOUS ATTITUDES: Macho (fast feathering, pressing to destination),
                        invulnerability (waving at the re-math),
                        impulsivity (fuel panel before airplane),
                        resignation (accepting the sequence, telling no one).
   TOTAL BRANCHES:      ~22 distinct paths
   TOTAL ENDINGS:       14 (2 full success, 6 qualified success,
                        2 friction/social cost, 1 delay/diversion,
                        1 aircraft damage, 1 off-airport survivable,
                        1 fatal, reachable only through 4+ consecutive
                        worst choices)
   MIN DECISION DEPTH:  4 story decisions on every path (audit enforces)
   TIMED DECISIONS:     No
   ESTIMATED DURATION:  20-30 minutes
   VERSION:             1.0    LAST REVIEWED: July 2026    REVIEWER: (pending)
   FUEL MATH (design):  Actual at engine start: L 46.5 / R 26.5 usable.
                        Partner's note claims R "about half," JPI totalizer
                        set to 74.0. Taxi+runup 0.9/side. Climb (17 min)
                        4.5/side. Cruise FF: L 10.4, R 11.3 (right runs
                        rich, on the squawk sheet). Right tank dry at 2:09
                        elapsed. Left at that moment: 21.7 gal. KELP 140 nm
                        ahead (61 min), KFST 46 nm behind (22 min with the
                        wind), KPEQ 24 nm (AWOS OTS, primary rwy closed).
                        Both engines fed from the left tank burn ~21.7 gph:
                        land KELP with ~2.7 gal, land KFST with ~14.
*/
<<set $pathArray to []>>
<<set $badchoices to 0>>
<<set $readWeather to false>>
<<set $readFlightPlan to false>>
<<set $readAircraft to false>>
<<set $readMap to false>>
<<set $fuelLeft to 46.5>>
<<set $fuelRight to 26.5>>
<<set $toppedOff to false>>
<<set $splashed to false>>
<<set $waltTexted to false>>
<<set $d2 to "">>
<<set $fuelSeen to false>>
<<set $rightSecured to false>>
<<set $featherFast to false>>
<<set $restored to false>>
<<set $airstart to false>>
<<set $declared to "none">>
<<set $crossfeedState to "normal">>
<<set $inversion to false>>
<<set $speedScare to false>>
<<set $headsDown to false>>
<<set $restumble to false>>
<<set $doubleScare to false>>
<<set $divert to "">>
